}} 'Simple file verification (SFV)' is a file format for storing CRC32 checksums
of files to verify the integrity of files. SFV is used to verify that a file has
not been corrupted, but it does not otherwise verify the file's authenticity.
The <tt>.sfv</tt> file extension is usually used for SFV files.
